File: South African born actress Charlize Theron has joined scores of people who congratulating the Springboks' win against England in the Rugby World Cup final on Saturday. JOHANNESBURG - South African born actress Charlize Theron has joined scores of people who are congratulating the Springboks' win against England in the Rugby World Cup final on Saturday. A proud Theron twitted a picture of the Springboks lifting the cup, with a message saying: "Sending so much love to these guys for a hard fought and well deserved #RWC win"   South Africa beat England 32 -12 to win their third RWC title. The Boks first lifted the Web Ellis Cup in 1995 and 2007 respectively and are now equal to their fiercest rivals, New Zealand.